replies.body:
{{champion:268}} {{item:3068}}

SHURIMA

Nah, seriously, what about making it an active instead that'd be something like a weaker Rammus ult where it deals an AoE burst with decreasing damage overtime. That way, Cinderhulk would remain the choice for jungling and tanks and bruisers would get the option being able to deal burst instead of sustained damage.

> were the three items that you can buy if you just want to not-die to specifically the adc. 

Why don't you go a ways back and see all the complaints everyone had that armor items did jack against ADCs because of {{item:3035}} 

It's not to say that makes anything that occurred good or bad, but citing that as if it was a fresh reason and hasn't always been that way is just artificially inflating an argument that doesn't hold much water anyway.

Kay the following make use of the Sunfire better then Deadmans Plate (or should build it)  {{champion:111}} {{champion:54}} {{champion:154}} {{champion:32}} {{champion:31}} {{champion:113}} 

And probably more I am forgetting about. 

And {{item:3143}} nagging needs to stop, this item is better now then before with that -10% crit reduction being so valuable against a lot of champions.
